title: double chocolate nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, oil and eggs.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Drop a teaspoonful onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
If desired, top each cookie with a pecan half.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until cookies test done with a toothpick. Cool on cookie sheet about 1 minute, then remove to rack to finish cooling.

title: stuffed turkey mushrooms
directions: Remove the stems on the mushrooms and chop.
Heat liquid Butter Buds in a skillet and cook the onion and ground turkey. Add the chopped mushroom stems and other ingredients.
Cook this mixture about 5 minutes.
Stuff this mixture into the mushroom caps and sprinkle with the grated cheese.
Preheat your broiler and place in oven for 2 to 4 minutes or until cheese melts. Yields 20 stuffed mushrooms.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt sugar and butter.
Add milk and boil 3 minutes.
Cool and add powdered sugar until thick enough to spread.

title: microwave "oven-fried" chicken
directions: Mix baking mix, paprika, salt and pepper; coat chicken. Arrange pieces, skin side up, in rectangular microwavable dish, 12 x 7 x 2-inch, with thickest parts to outside edges.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High 10 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn.
Microwave 8 to 12 minutes longer.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture alternately with buttermilk, starting and ending with flour.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and jello and set aside while preparing fruit.
Mix fruit and cheese mixture.
Lightly mix one medium sized carton Cool Whip and pour in mold or container (for me a mold does not work because it does not set enough for a mold).
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Will keep for 3 or 4 days.

title: basil bread sticks
directions: Cut loaf in half (5 x 4-inch).
Then cut each half in half (sandwich style).
Cut each sandwich style half into 3 (1-inch) wedges 5-inches long, total of 12 wedges 1 x 5-inch long.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spread mix on all cut sides of bread wedges.
Space on ungreased cookie sheets and bake at 425° for 7 to 9 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm.

title: peanut-cheese-raisin sandwiches
directions: Spread one side of bread slices with butter. Broil 6-inches from heat until lightly browned. Set aside.
Combine peanut butter and remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Spread mixture on untoasted side of 5 bread slices.
Top each with another slice, toasted side up.
Yields 5 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Cut chicken in chunks. Grate cheese.
In a lightly greased 2-quart casserole, place a layer of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; spread on top of broccoli.
Place a layer of chicken on top of soup mixture; sprinkle with cheese.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over all; dot with butter.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stromboli
directions: Smash bread down and roll into large rectangle (10 x 15-inch). Brush with olive oil and sprinkle with oregano.
Lay on cheese and meat slices.
Sprinkle with additional Cheddar cheese.

title: crunchy ice cream pie
directions: Mix until blended, reserve 1/4 cup.
Press in pie pan to form crust.
Add ice cream and sprinkle 1/4 cup on top.
Put in freezer 4 to 6 hours.
Ready to serve.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, beaten egg yolks, sugar, salt and spices. Gradually add scalded milk and mix thoroughly.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour mixture into unbaked crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Place vanilla caramels, water and oleo in the top of a double boiler.
Heat, stirring frequently, until the caramels are melted and the sauce is smooth.
Combine slightly beaten eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Gradually add the caramel sauce, mixing well. Add pecan halves.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; continue baking for 30 minutes.
The pie filling will appear to be very soft while hot, but will become firm as it cools.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix flour, sugar, margarine, and pecans.
Press into baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions.
Beat in powdered sugar, blend in cream cheese and pour over the crust.
Refrigerate at least 2 or 3 hours until well set.
Spoon cherry pie filling over top.

title: quick and easy coffee cake
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cup biscuit mix, sugar and pecans in mixing bowl.
Add milk, egg, vanilla and oil.
Beat by hand, mixing well. Pour onto greased 8-inch round baking dish suitable for microwave cooking.
Combine remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over batter.
Micro cook 4 to 7 minutes on High.
Rotating dish a half turn after 2 minutes.
Check for doneness at 4 minutes.
The cake is done when the top is almost dry and springs back when touched.
Cool 15 minutes; drizzle with Orange Glaze.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Beat in eggs and add nuts, coconut, vanilla wafers (crushed) and vanilla.
Bake at 270° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream Deuteronomy with Jeremiah 6:20 until light.
Add the 3 Jeremiah 17:11 one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add the 1 Samuel 14:25.
Sift and measure Judges 15:1.
Take 2 cups of it and sift it with the Leviticus, Amos and 2 Chronicles.
Blend the remaining Judges 15:1 with 1 Samuel 30:12, Nahum and Numbers and set aside.
Add the sifted mixture to the creamed mixture, alternating with Judges 5:25.
Stir in the reserved mixture of 1 Samuel, Nahum and Numbers.
Bake in a loaf pan for 1 hour at 325°. Glaze top with additional 1 Samuel 14:25 and slivered, toasted Numbers.

title: salted nut rolls
directions: Cream the marshmallow cream and vanilla together.
Blend in the powdered sugar.
Begin blending with mixer, then work in with hands until all the sugar is blended in.
Shape into rolls 1/2 x 1 1/2-inches long.
Freeze rolls 2 to 3 hours until frozen hard. Melt the caramels with the cream.
Dip rolls in caramel and then in chopped dry roasted peanuts.
Lay out on a tray and freeze.
After they are frozen, put into a large plastic bag and keep frozen until you need them.

title: noon on the equator (non-alcoholic drink)
directions: Combine all ingredients in cocktail shaker and add ice cubes. Shake well and strain into glasses.
Makes 1 serving.

title: crunchy imperial chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend crumbs, cheese, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
Dip each piece of chicken in butter, then in crumb mixture.
Arrange in open shallow baking dish.
Place any remaining ingredients over chicken.
Bake one hour.
Do not turn chicken.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat the egg yolks; stir in the sweetened condensed milk, lime juice and a few drops of green food coloring.
In a small bowl, stiffly beat 1 egg white; fold into the milk mixture.
Turn into baked and cooled 8 or 9-inch pastry shell.

Beat 3 egg whites with cream of tartar until foamy; gradually beat in the sugar, one tablespoon at a time, until meringue is stiff, but not dry. Spread on top of pie, sealing carefully to edge of shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until meringue is golden.
Cool. Chill before serving.

title: slim 'n trim pumpkin pie
directions: Preparation:
Combine ingredients and pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 50 minutes.
Yield:
Six 117 calorie servings.

title: german chocolate sandwich cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, butter, cocoa, baking soda, salt, eggs, milk and vanilla. Beat at medium speed until blended. Stir in pecans. Drop dough into 1-1/4 inch balls on ungreased cookie sheet. flatten slightly. Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until almost set. Cool slightly; remove to wire rack. Cool completely. Prepare filling. Spread flat side of one cookie with 1 heaping tablespoon of filling; cover with flat side of second cookie. Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup and remaining ingredients; shape into 6 patties.
In skillet, brown patties (use shortening if necessary); pour off fat.
Blend in remaining soup and 1/3 cup water.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes or until done.
Stir often. Makes 6 servings.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Stir in eggs, milk, bread pieces, salt, mustard and cheese.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased casserole pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: reception punch for 100
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add orange and lemon slices, if desired. Pour over ice in punch bowl.

title: low country stew
directions: Place sausage in very large, deep pot.
Cover with water, then add corn, red pepper, Old Bay seasoning and
Old Bay seasoning bag.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add potatoes and beer.
Cook for 1 hour, then add shrimp.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: angel's delight
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Let stand until starts to gel.
Beat Milnot until whipped.
Add jello mixture. Beat well.
Pour over crushed vanilla wafers.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
May top with a few crushed wafers.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add onions.
Cook until soft (10 minutes).
Add rice.
Put rice mixture into casserole dish.
Add consomme and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not cover.

title: baked pineapple chicken
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice. Combine reserved juice with garlic, cornstarch, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and rosemary. Arrange chicken in shallow baking pan.
Broil chicken until browned.
Stir sauce, pour over chicken and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Arrange lemon and pineapple slices around chicken. Spoon sauce from baking pan over chicken and continue baking 5 minutes longer.
Garnish with fresh parsley.

title: pineapple walnut cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour all ingredients into a bowl and mix thoroughly by hand.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Or pour into 11 x 16-inch cookie sheet and bake a 350° for 20 minutes.

title: red pepper jelly
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar, peppers and juice to a boil.
Boil 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add Certo and green or red food coloring.
Stir.
Put in jars and seal.
(Use only Certo.)

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Soak together for 1 hour in large bowl, poppy seed and milk; add and beat the eggs, oil, sugar and almond extract.
Mix separately both flours, milk powder and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients to wet.
Mix. Bake in greased and floured cake pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
If desired ice with xxxx sugar icing with lemon juice.

title: chili-o-dip
directions: Brown beef with bell pepper.
Add other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Serve with chips.
(May pour into crock-pot to keep warm.)

title: blackened catfish
directions: Put spices in a 1 gallon food storage bag.
Close bag and shake well.
Put 1 fillet in bag at a time and shake.
Coat large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Add oil and heat over medium heat.
Add catfish fillets, skinned side up, and cook 4 to 5 minutes until lightly blackened.
Turn with spatula.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes longer, until fish feels firm.
Serve with lemon slices.

title: carrot pennies
directions: Slice and cook carrots until tender.
Combine oil, vinegar, sugar and soup.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over carrots, onion and peppers.
Best if marinates overnight.
Will keep for several days.

title: barbecue beef bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook ground beef and 1/2 cup of the onion in 10-inch skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce.
Spoon into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; sprinkle with cheese.

title: chicken ramen
directions: Cook chicken, debone and cut into small pieces (reserve 1/2 cup
liquid).
Cook
noodles; drain and add packet.
Cook broccoli;
drain.

title: breakfast brunch
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain well.
Line a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with crescent rolls.
Press edges together.
Sprinkle with sausage and Mozzarella cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, then sprinkle with 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Put back in oven for 5 minutes.

title: party chicken
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Tear dried beef and spread in bottom of dish.
Wrap bacon around rolled up 1/2 of chicken breast. Place on beef.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Pour over chicken.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 250° to 275° for 3 hours, uncovered.

title: tomato marmalade
directions: Select 4 quarts of firm, ripe tomatoes.
Peel and slice thin. Wash 6 lemons, slice and remove seeds, leaving the peel on.
Put in a saucepan with the tomatoes, lemons, raisins and sugar.
Cook slowly for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until mixture is thick.
Put in small glasses (sterile) and cover with paraffin.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground chuck and onions. Add other ingredients and simmer for at least 1 hour.

title: u.s. 31 barbecues
directions: Cook meat slowly until tender and falls apart.
Mix all ingredients and cook in slow cooker for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
This is better if you can slow cook overnight.

title: ice cream wafers
directions: Blend sugar and shortening.
Add egg, beaten until velvety. Add flour and salt.
Beat vigorously.
Add flavoring.
Mix.

title: italian zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini and remove ends.
Do not peel and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Cut onion and pepper into rings.
Heat oil in 12-inch skillet.
Place zucchini in skillet and brown lightly on both sides.
Add onion and green pepper.
Sprinkle in salt, garlic salt, pepper and oregano.
Top with tomatoes.
Cover and bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle cheese over vegetables.
Simmer 15 minutes or until zucchini is tender and a fairly thick sauce.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Sprinkle flour over meat and place in crock-pot.
Cut up veggies and place on meat.

title: gingerbread dumplings
directions: Bring applesauce to a boil. Add enough water to gingerbread mix to make a thick batter. Drop batter by spoonfuls into boiling applesauce. Cover and cook slowly until gingerbread is baked.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Chop up the vegetables.
Blend other ingredients and mix with vegetables.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar.
Add rest of ingredients to egg mixture and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
While hot, cover with marshmallow cream.
Let cool.

title: oven barbecued chicken(light)
directions: Place chicken pieces, skin sides up, in ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in 375° oven 30 minutes.
Spoon sauce over chicken; bake, uncovered, until thickest pieces are done, about 30 minutes longer.
Yields 6 servings, 204 calories each.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve jello and Knox gelatine completely in boiling water. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cool until firm, then cut into squares.

title: cornbread(a.k.a. yellow brownies)
directions: Combine Bisquick, cornmeal and sugar.
Add eggs, then add milk.
Beat well.
Mix in melted butter or margarine.
Place batter in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: special veggie casserole
directions: Bake at 300° until bread crumbs are brown, about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a full boil (3 to 4 minutes). Quickly drop mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Cool completely. Store in refrigerator. Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: hot mocha mix
directions: Combine all
ingredients and mix well.	Store mix in an airtight container.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and peanuts and cook 4 minutes on High.
Add vanilla and butter.
Cook 4 minutes more on High or until caramel colors.
Add soda; pour onto greased cookie sheet.

title: chicken divan pot pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 425°.
Remove pie crust from freezer.
Invert one crust onto waxed paper and let thaw.

title: nectarine-brandy sorbet
directions: Puree nectarines in blender to measure about 3 to 4 cups.
Add sugar; heat slowly in saucepan until sugar dissolves.
Stir brandy, lemon juice and zest into puree and pour into canister of ice cream freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's directions. Makes about 10 servings.

title: boiled ham dinner
directions: Cook ham (can use leftovers) with carrots and potatoes seasoned with a little garlic powder, salt and black pepper.
When these lack about 15 minutes cooking, add quartered onion and cabbage.
Lay these on top and steam until cabbage is cooked.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and milk together.
Add cherries to the mixture.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with wire whip.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and freeze overnight.
Take out of freezer 15 to 20 minutes before serving.
Can be refrozen.
Can use strawberry, cherry or blueberry filling.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil and strawberries. Stir until moist.
Spoon into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Do not cook too long, just until edges are starting to harden and draw away from the sides.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
A favorite for Afghanistan.

title: meat and cheese tortillas
directions: Cook ground beef until brown and crumbly; drain.
Combine meat, cottage cheese, 1/2 cup Italian sauce, green pepper, onion, olives and flour.
Season and mix well.

title: layered salad
directions: Place torn lettuce pieces on bottom.
Cauliflower pieces on next layer.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and Parmesan cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread mixture on top of lettuce, cauliflower and onions.
Seal.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add bacon just before tossing.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and cool.
Cook bacon and crumble or chop.
Combine all ingredients.
Marinate several hours in refrigerator.
Add dressing and a little garlic powder.

title: dessert or salad
directions: Mix all together and chill thoroughly before using.
Can be frozen and served as dessert.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients but cheese.
Pour half in large greased skillet.
Then add grated cheese.
Then pour remaining mix on top. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter and then dump
rest of ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: cream cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with 1 teaspoon of salt until tender.
Drain and mash potatoes.
Blend in rest of ingredients.
Put in 3-quart casserole.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: red, white and blue jello salad
directions: First Layer:
Make 1 box raspberry jello with 1 3/4 cups hot water as usual.
Pour into mold.
Set 2 hours.

title: polish meatballs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and form into very small balls.
Place in oblong pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs. Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in preheated 350° oven.
Cover them for the first hour of baking.

title: pat's apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed.
Add nectar last.
Mix well, pour into a greased and floured bundt pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, melted butter and 1/4 cup sugar. Press in 9 x 13-inch dish and bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Cool COMPLETELY. Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip together. Spread over crushed pretzels. Chill in freezer until completely firm (not frozen). Dissolve Jell-O in water. Stir in strawberries. Mix until thawed, then add pineapple. Chill until firm.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Mix and simmer to thickness desired.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar,
cocoa, milk and butter.
Boil rapidly 1 1/2 minutes, stirring
all the time.
Add oatmeal, nuts and vanilla. Drop while hot on wax paper.
Cool.
Yields 50 cookies.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Grasp tick with thumb and finger and gently pull.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chow mein noodles.
Put in ungreased casserole dish; sprinkle chow mein noodles on top with a little margarine.
Bake at 350° until hot, about 30 to 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.
Freezes well.

title: uncle jim's whipped turnip puff
directions: Mix all ingredients together very well.
Spoon into greased 6-cup casserole dish and brush the top with a little butter.
Bake in 375° moderate oven for 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: summer sausage
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Divide mixture into 4 equal parts. Make a roll out of each part.
(Roll will be approximately 2 inches in diameter and about 3 inches long.)
Wrap each roll individually in foil, being sure the dull side is out. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Punch holes on bottom of each roll and place on a broiler pan.
Put 1/2-inch of water in bottom of pan. Bake at 325° for 90 minutes.
Let cool enough to handle, re-wrap and refrigerate.
(Can also be frozen.)

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Place potato slice on large piece of foil; cover with onion. Add seasonings.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon and dot with butter.
Wrap foil tightly.
Cook about 1 hour on grill or until potatoes are done; turn several times.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hamburger pot pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in Crisco.
Stir in green beans, soup and seasonings.
Pour filling into onion pastry lined pie plate. Bake as directed.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Combine rice-vermicelli mix with ground beef and eggs.
Shape into meatballs in large skillet.
Brown meat balls and drain off grease.
Combine contents of seasoning packet and water.
Pour over meat balls.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until thick gravy forms.

title: 7-up pork chops
directions: Season pork chops. Place in a shallow pan. Pour 7-Up over them. Sprinkle soup mix on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. LIGHTEN-UP BONELESS CHICKEN BREAST

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw and drain the spinach. Melt the butter. Add all the ingredients and mix well with hands. Roll into balls and cook at 350 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ladyfinger dessert with cream cheese and pineapple
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add sugar and mix until smooth.
Add well drained pineapple, then the Cool Whip.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and celery; drain well.
Set aside.
Cook onion slowly in butter until tender.
Add soup, milk and cheese.
Cook over medium heat, stirring well until cheese melts.
Stir in rice, broccoli and celery.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish which has been buttered.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: best pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar.
Whip until light, beating well after each addition.
Add 2 eggs at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately, then add vanilla with mixer on low speed.
Pour batter into slightly greased and floured 10-inch tube pan; bake 1 1/2 hours to cook.
Bake in 325° oven.

title: cheddar cheese pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: Place English muffins on cookie sheet.
Spread pizza sauce on top of each muffin half.
Add pizza topping as desired.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 15 minutes or until muffin is toasted and cheese is melted.

title: vegetable macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and cool.
Add vegetables and mix well. Combine milk, vinegar, sugar, mayo, salt and pepper.
Add to macaroni mixture.
Chill at least 4 hours before serving.
Better if left overnight.
Keeps well.
Serves 10.

title: vickie's cheesy bacon potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in oven or microwave until done.
Slice into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Salt and pepper. Sprinkle with cheese.
Crumble bacon on top of cheese.
Bake approximately 10 minutes at 350° until cheese is bubbly.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: italian beef sandwiches
directions: In a deep baking pan, place roast and 1-inch of water. Sprinkle with salt and cover with onions. Bake, covered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat from pan. Reserve and chill broth.
Refrigerate meat until firm.
Cut into very thin slices.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Add sugar, tomato paste, tomatoes and garlic.
Cook down until "dry enough".
Add bread crumbs until "dry like you want it" (about 1 cup).
Bake in a Pyrex dish.
Freezes well.

title: no bake cake
directions: Crumble cake and spread evenly in bottom of large pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Pour pineapple over top; heat milk and marshmallows until dissolved.
Pour over the layer of pineapple.
When ready to serve, put Cool Whip over top.
Then sprinkle with coconut.

title: bran muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients, except All-Bran.
Mix All-Bran, milk, oil and egg whites together and let sit 5 minutes.
Stir dry ingredients into wet mixture.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin cups or line cups with paper liners.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Layer noodles, sliced hard-boiled eggs, peas and tuna.
Heat mushroom soup and milk to boiling and pour over mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Combine all ingredients except candy kisses.
Mix until dough forms.
Shape into balls (1 teaspoon).
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Top each cookie immediately with a candy kiss.
Press down firmly so that cookie cracks around the edge.

title: bev's lemon bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, margarine and powdered sugar in small bowl.
Press evenly in bottom and about 3/8-inch up sides of an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
(If dough is sticky, flour fingers.)
Bake 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients in a medium bowl on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Pour over hot crust and bake until no indentation remains when touched lightly in center, about 25 minutes.
Let stand until cool; cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes 25 squares.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl with hands; shape into a large ball.
Roll in ground pecans and parsley flakes.
Freeze 24 hours.

title: elegant scalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven about an hour.
Sprinkle paprika on top, also, before baking, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: date nut torte
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, mix dates, walnuts, flour and sugar.
In small bowl at high speed, beat eggs for 5 minutes or until thick and lemon colored.
Stir into date mixture. Batter will be very thick.
Spread evenly in well-buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until wooden spoon comes out clean.
Cool and then cut into squares.

title: slow cooker brisket
directions: Place brisket in crock-pot, cutting meat if necessary to fit into pot. In a bowl, stir together all other ingredients and pour over meat. Cover; cook on low heat setting about 10 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat, reserving juices; cover to keep warm.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, melted margarine, sour cream, soup, onion and cheese.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan and top with crushed potato chips.
Pour the reserved 1/4 stick melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Blend
first
4 ingredients.
Add 5 slices white bread, cubed and
one No. 2 can crushed pineapple, drained.
Mix all thoroughly and bake in a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole for 45 minutes at 350°.
Good with ham.

title: pasta salad
directions: Pour olive oil into wooden salad bowl.
Squeeze approximately 2 tablespoons of lemon juice into bowl.
Whisk together.
Add salt, pepper, Parmesan and a pressed clove of garlic to taste. Toss with rest of ingredients and enjoy!

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. In a large bowl, mix long grain rice, mushroom soup, celery soup, water, parsley and curry powder. Pour into baking pan or casserole.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix. Cover and seal with foil.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours.
Do not open until ready to serve.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: lite mushroom stuffed potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; dry, prick with fork and bake in 425° oven for 65 minutes or until soft.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Mix everything together but chocolate chips.
Add chips last. Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and marshmallow cream together with a mixer.
Cut up fruit and serve with dip at room temperature.

title: sausage minestrone soup
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, brown sausage, onion and garlic.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients except beans, spaghetti and cheese. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 1 hour. Stir in beans and spaghetti.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes or until spaghetti and green beans are tender.
Serve with Parmesan cheese. Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble cookies in blender.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and margarine.
In another bowl, mix the pudding with the milk and Cool Whip.
Combine cream cheese with pudding.
Put paper plate in the bottom of a clay flower pot and starting with the Oreo cookie crumbs, alternate layers of pudding and cookies, ending with cookies on top.
For a touch of realism, add artificial flowers and a spade for decoration.
Can also use gummy worms.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add Velveeta and margarine.
Stir until blended over low heat.
Pour into casserole.
Crumble Ritz crackers; mix with 1/2 stick margarine.
Top the broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites in a bowl; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar. Add egg yolks.
Beat well.
Sift flour.
Measure.
Sift again with soda and salt.
Alternately add flour and sour cream to egg mixture, a little at a time.
Fold in beaten egg whites and vanilla (almond and lemon, if desired).
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients
thoroughly until mixture boils, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over about 6 quarts of popped popcorn. Add peanuts to taste.
Put in a large roasting pan and bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chocolate yum yum dessert
directions: Mix together the flour, butter, nuts and sugar and pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass
pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Combine the powdered sugar, 2 cups topping and cream cheese in electric mixer and beat at low speed until well blended.
Spread on cooled bottom layer.
Beat the 2 packages of instant pudding with 3 cups milk and spread on cream cheese layer.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Mix butter and sugar together until creamy. Add spices and blend thoroughly. Mixture must be kept in the refrigerator.

title: peanut butter roundups
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Add and beat eggs. Add and blend the peanut butter.
Stir into mixture the flour, salt and soda.
Add oats.
Add last the Rice Krispies.
Make small balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press with a fork to make crisscross.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until the way you like them.

title: baked chicken with sour cream
directions: Wrap each chicken piece with a slice of chipped beef, then wrap with bacon.
Place chicken in greased casserole dish and pour soup/sour cream mixture over.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 hours.
Serve with green salad or fruit salad.

title: simple and delicious sesame seed dressing
directions: Toast seeds in 200° oven until light brown.
Combine next 5 ingredients in blender.
Add vinegar and oil slowly.
Pour into a jar.
Add seed and refrigerate.
Best the next day!
Enjoy!

title: mexican trash appetizer
directions: Mix together the above ingredients. Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add 4 tablespoons vinegar and 6 tablespoons oil.
Marinate.
Chill.
Drain and then serve with tortilla chips.

title: grandma's german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in water; set side to cool.
Cream the Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add cooled chocolate.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk to the creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool and turn onto a cake plate.

title: chicken and macaroni cheese casserole
directions: Melt butter with onions in saucepan.
Add soup and milk.
Add cheese (1/2 cup).
In a 9 x 12-inch pan, have chicken and macaroni.
Stir in soup mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake until melted.

title: butterscotch pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients, then add those remaining. Cook over medium heat until thick in double boiler. Pour into two prebaked pie shells and top with meringue.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spanish bean soup
directions: Dice potatoes and onion.
Combine all the ingredients in large pot with lid and simmer for 3 hours.
Serve with Cuban bread.

title: cherry torte
directions: Beat egg whites very stiff along with cream of tartar.
Slowly add sugar and vanilla.
Fold in nuts and crackers.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in and spread evenly.
Bake about 24 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.
If using Dream Whip, whip and spread on torte. Top with pie filling.
Chill 4 hours.
Can be kept several days in refrigerator without getting soggy.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar, water and seeds for 1 minute and let cool completely.

title: blue cheese meat loaf roll
directions: Tear the bread into small pieces.
Combine bread and milk; stir in cheese and 1 egg.
Set aside.

title: grilled chevron chops(beef goat chops)
directions: Marinate loin or rib chops in a mixture of equal amounts of balsamic vinegar, olive oil, and dijon mustard for several hours in the refrigerator and then barbecue.

title: ribbon cake
directions: Sift flour and cream of tartar 3 times.
Beat all together. Divide into 3 parts, leaving 2 layers white.
To third part, add molasses.
Add cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt oleo and cocoa. Stir in sugar, eggs, flour, salt and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Cool.
Butter a pan (do not flour).
Take out of oven and cover with marshmallows.
Let them melt. Put on icing.

title: unbelievable lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients, except coconut, in blender and run on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Place in oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Cook box of raisins with enough water to cover raisins.
Add sugar and cornstarch to thicken; cook for 7 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs; add vanilla and milk.
Add baking powder and salt to flour.
Mix well.
When dough is stiff enough, roll out thin.
Cut with cookie cutter; put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Put a spoonful of raisins on and then put another on the top.
Make a vent on top and bake 6 to 10 minutes in 400° oven.

title: sherry cake
directions: Mix all for 5 minutes.
Pour in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes and remove. Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. If desired, place slices of bacon on top.

title: chicken creole
directions: Cook chicken with bay leaves.

Remove bay leaves; debone and chop the chicken. Combine vegetables, half the oleo, tomato sauce and seasonings; simmer until vegetables are tender. Add the chopped chicken. Melt the remaining oleo in a skillet; blend in the flour and cook until brown. Add 1 cup broth, stirring until thickened. Add to the chicken mixture and serve over rice or noodles. Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate County Line and Colby cheeses.
Leave setting at room temperature for 2 hours.
Blend together with remaining ingredients.
Form into ball.
Sprinkle with paprika and roll in crushed walnuts.
Chill.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix first three ingredients until blended and pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Brush beaten egg over the top of bread and continue baking for 15 minutes more. Yields 1 loaf.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown roast in shortening in Dutch oven.
Combine onion soup mix with 2 cups water.
Pour over roast; simmer, turning occasionally for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.
Add vegetables and cook until potatoes are tender.
Remove roast onto serving dish.
Blend flour and remaining water.
Stir into gravy.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until thickened.
